git-clone

<repository>  <directory>

--local/--no-local/--no-hardlinks
objects are hardlinked, this can save disk space,
Shared and it is safe to move/remove/modify original
repository.

--shared/--reference <repository>
like Symbolic link, not safe and it is not recommended
to use this option

--branch
Instead of pointing the newlu created HEAD to the branch
pointed by cloned repository's HEAD, point to <name> branch
instead.

--depth
create a shallow clone with specified number of revisons.

--bared/mirror
Create a bared reporsitory.
